---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Earned Media Skills — by 701am"
  description="An open-source library of 28 AI agent skills for earned media, journalist outreach, and PR. Free. MIT licensed. Built for Claude Code and Claude Cowork."
>

  <!-- ════ MASTHEAD ════ -->
  <header class="skills-masthead">
    <div class="masthead-inner">
      <p class="skills-eyebrow">
        <span class="skills-rule"></span>
        § Earned Media Skills · by 701am
        <span class="skills-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <h1 class="skills-title">
        The PR system<br />
        that works in <em>plain English.</em>
      </h1>
      <p class="skills-deck">
        Twenty-eight AI agent skills for earned media, journalist outreach,
        and the long work of being remembered. Free. Open source. No framework,
        no runtime, no setup beyond the clone.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead-meta">
        <span class="meta-pill">MIT License</span>
        <span class="meta-dot">·</span>
        <span class="meta-text">28 skills</span>
        <span class="meta-dot">·</span>
        <span class="meta-text">Built for Claude Code &amp; Cowork</span>
      </div>
      <div class="masthead-cta">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://github.com/701am/earned-media-skills">
          Clone on GitHub
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#install">
          Or skip to the install
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE OPENING SCENE ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--paper">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 01 — A scene</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="scene">
      <p class="scene-stamp">9:47 a.m. · Wednesday · Some newsroom</p>
      <p class="scene-prose dropcap">
        The reporter is on her second coffee. She has eighty-one unread emails,
        a deadline at three, and an editor who wants the draft by lunch. She is
        scanning subject lines. <em>Re: circling back.</em> Delete.
        <em>Quick question.</em> Delete. <em>Hope this finds you well —</em>
        delete before she even reads the rest. By the time she stops scrolling
        she has dispatched seventeen pitches in under a minute, and she has not
        opened one of them.
      </p>
      <p class="scene-prose">
        She did not delete them because she is callous. She deleted them because
        every single subject line told her, in advance, that the body would not
        be worth her time. <em>The shape of the pitch betrayed it.</em>
      </p>
      <p class="scene-prose">
        This is the problem. Not that pitches don't get sent.
        That they don't get <em>read.</em>
      </p>
      <div class="scene-fold"></div>
      <p class="scene-prose scene-prose--quiet">
        Earned media is the coverage you cannot buy — the feature, the quote,
        the citation, the moment a third party decided your work was worth
        their reader's attention. It carries more weight than any ad you will
        ever run. Getting it consistently is a craft, and the craft begins
        with the subject line a working reporter does not delete at 9:47 a.m.
        on a Wednesday.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — WHY GENERIC AI DOESN'T WORK ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--warm">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 02 — The diagnosis</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="diagnosis">
      <h2 class="diagnosis-h">
        Reporters can <em>tell.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="diagnosis-lede">
        You have tried it. You ran a prompt. The model produced something
        plausible-sounding. You read it again and felt — what's the word —
        embarrassed. Not because the grammar was wrong. Because every working
        reporter on earth has seen this exact email five hundred times.
      </p>

      <p class="diagnosis-label">The tells, in the order they get spotted:</p>
      <ol class="diagnosis-list">
        <li><strong>The vocabulary.</strong> Leverage. Robust. Transformative. Seamless. Innovative. Solutions. Empowering. Cutting-edge. Words that announce, in advance, that no human chose them.</li>
        <li><strong>The opener.</strong> "I hope this email finds you well." It does not. She is on deadline.</li>
        <li><strong>The subject.</strong> The hook is buried six words deep, behind a participle, after a hedge. By then, gone.</li>
        <li><strong>The framing.</strong> The pitch leads with the sender. Not the story. Not the reader. Not why anyone outside the company should care.</li>
        <li><strong>The follow-up.</strong> "Just circling back!" — adding nothing, asking again, costing her another half-second of attention that she did not have to spare.</li>
      </ol>

      <p class="diagnosis-close">
        These are not stylistic preferences. They are <em>signals</em>. Each one
        tells a reader, in two seconds or less, that the next ten minutes of
        their life is not what is in the body of this email. They learn to
        delete by shape.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE REMEDY ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--paper">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 03 — What this is</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="remedy">
      <h2 class="remedy-h">
        A library of <em>skills</em> — not a tool, not a SaaS, not a workflow.
      </h2>

      <div class="remedy-grid">
        <div class="remedy-col">
          <h4 class="remedy-sub">Plain markdown, on your machine.</h4>
          <p>
            Each skill is a folder with one file: <code>SKILL.md</code>. Your
            agent reads it and follows it. No framework. No runtime. No
            configuration. Clone the repo. Point Claude at the folder. It works.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="remedy-col">
          <h4 class="remedy-sub">Client context is the foundation.</h4>
          <p>
            One skill — <code>client-context</code> — holds the client's voice,
            proof points, angle library, journalist history, and competitive
            landscape. Every other skill reads it first. That is why the output
            sounds like <em>your</em> client wrote it, not a template did.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="remedy-col">
          <h4 class="remedy-sub">Memory compounds in the open.</h4>
          <p>
            Pitches sent, replies received, placements logged — all in plain
            markdown, in an Obsidian vault you can read with your own eyes.
            The system gets smarter each week because it remembers what it
            already tried.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="remedy-col">
          <h4 class="remedy-sub">A humanizer at the end of the pipe.</h4>
          <p>
            Before any outreach output reaches you, it runs through a
            twenty-four-pattern check. The leverage, the seamless, the
            <em>I hope this finds you,</em> the buried hook — caught and
            removed. What you see is what a journalist sees.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — WHO USES IT ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--warm">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 04 — Four desks</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="desks">
      <h2 class="desks-h">
        Four <em>desks</em> this is for.
      </h2>

      <div class="desks-grid">
        <article class="desk">
          <p class="desk-num">№ 01</p>
          <h3 class="desk-h">The founder doing her own PR.</h3>
          <p class="desk-p">
            You know your story better than any agency could in three months
            of onboarding. You don't need a strategist. You need the system to
            run the parts that are <em>craft</em> — the right journalist for
            this angle, the pitch under a hundred and fifty words, the
            follow-up that adds a fact instead of asking again. The skills
            handle the craft. You handle the relationships.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="desk">
          <p class="desk-num">№ 02</p>
          <h3 class="desk-h">The in-house comms team that won't hire.</h3>
          <p class="desk-p">
            You can run a structured program — weekly monitor, thirty-day
            editorial calendar, disciplined outreach, monthly report your CEO
            will actually read — without adding headcount. The portfolio
            manager gives you visibility across product lines or business units
            simultaneously. One operator. Full coverage.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="desk">
          <p class="desk-num">№ 03</p>
          <h3 class="desk-h">The agency that wants a memory.</h3>
          <p class="desk-p">
            One vault per client. The portfolio manager scans every client
            simultaneously and tells you which reporter is being pitched by
            two different accounts this week, which angle type is landing
            across the book, which client has gone quiet. The kind of
            cross-client awareness you cannot have from inside any single
            engagement.
          </p>
        </article>

        <article class="desk">
          <p class="desk-num">№ 04</p>
          <h3 class="desk-h">The skeptic who tried AI and quit.</h3>
          <p class="desk-p">
            You ran a prompt. The output was generic. You closed the tab. Fair.
            The client-context layer and the humanizer were built for exactly
            this problem. The output is specific because it is built from the
            client's actual voice and tested angles. Then every word runs
            through the twenty-four-pattern check. Try it once. If it still
            sounds like a robot wrote it, walk.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 05 — THE 28 SKILLS ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--paper" id="skills">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 05 — The shelf</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="shelf-intro">
      <h2 class="shelf-h">
        Twenty-eight skills, <em>organized by use.</em>
      </h2>
      <p class="shelf-deck">
        Each one is a single markdown file. Read them. Fork them. Rewrite them
        for the way <em>your</em> desk works.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="shelf">
      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Foundation</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">client-context</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">intake</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">The memory layer every other skill reads, and the onboarding that builds it from conversation.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Strategy</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">earned-media-strategy</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">editorial-calendar</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">competitive-intelligence</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">The full program plan, the thirty-day calendar, the competitive landscape — written down.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Research</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">journalist-research</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">data-researcher</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Finding the right reporters and the original data angles that give a story its hook.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Campaign</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">digital-pr-ideation</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">visual-gap-hunter</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">seo-pr</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Original research campaigns, editorial link-building, earned media that also builds authority.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Outreach</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">pitch-writer</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">press-release</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">newsjacking</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Every format a journalist receives — including the rapid response with a window of hours.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row shelf-row--highlight">
        <div class="shelf-label">Quality</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">humanizer</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">The twenty-four-pattern check that runs on every outreach output before you ever see it.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Relationships</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">infinite-follow-up</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">influencer-mapper</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">tiktok-influencer</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">The follow-up sequence, the creator landscape, the DM that does not sound like one.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Content</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">thought-leadership</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">podcast-placements</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">speaking-events</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">media-training</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Op-eds, guest appearances, conference slots, and interview prep — grounded in real proof.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Links</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">link-reclamation</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Converting unlinked brand mentions and broken backlinks into proper links.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Defense</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">crisis-comms</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">monitor</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Crisis response with a holding statement first and human review always required, and the daily scan that scores opportunities before your workday starts.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Recognition</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">award-submissions</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Submissions grounded in real proof. Does not inflate. Exaggerated submissions get disqualified.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Measurement</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">roi-measurement</span>
          <span class="shelf-item">client-reporting</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">Full program measurement. Monthly reports in business language — including the section about what didn't work, because that is the section that earns trust.</div>
      </div>

      <div class="shelf-row">
        <div class="shelf-label">Portfolio</div>
        <div class="shelf-items">
          <span class="shelf-item">portfolio-manager</span>
        </div>
        <div class="shelf-note">The cross-client consciousness layer. Detects journalist conflicts, surfaces angle patterns, flags stalled accounts. Requires memory.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 06 — THE PROCLAMATION ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--proclamation">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 06 — The rule</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="proclamation">
      <p class="proc-stamp">★ Read aloud at the desk, every morning ★</p>
      <p class="proc-h">
        Every output must pass one <em>test.</em>
      </p>
      <p class="proc-q">
        Would a journalist feel <em>respected</em> receiving this?
      </p>
      <div class="proc-rule"></div>
      <p class="proc-p">
        If the pitch inflates the client's importance, if the press release
        reads as promotion, if the follow-up adds nothing new — the skill
        says so before producing the work. You fix it or you do not send it.
      </p>
      <p class="proc-p">
        This is not a constraint placed upon the system. It <em>is</em> the
        system. Reporters who learn — over months, over years — that the
        pitches arriving from a sender are worth their time will open them
        on sight. That trust is the asset. The trust is what earned media
        actually is.
      </p>
      <p class="proc-sig">— The desk at 701am</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 07 — INSTALL ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--install" id="install">
    <div class="section-label">
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
      <div class="label-text">§ 07 — How to begin</div>
      <div class="label-bar"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="install">
      <h2 class="install-h">
        Three commands. Then it runs.
      </h2>

      <ol class="install-steps">
        <li>
          <span class="install-num">i.</span>
          <div class="install-step-body">
            <h4>Clone the repository.</h4>
            <pre class="install-code">git clone https://github.com/701am/earned-media-skills.git</pre>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="install-num">ii.</span>
          <div class="install-step-body">
            <h4>Open Claude Code from the project folder. Run intake.</h4>
            <pre class="install-code">"Run the intake skill for [client name]"</pre>
            <p class="install-note">
              Intake asks one question at a time — business, voice, founding
              story, product proof, angle history, competitors. Answer honestly.
              At the end you have a client context file every other skill reads.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="install-num">iii.</span>
          <div class="install-step-body">
            <h4>Or use it inside Claude Cowork.</h4>
            <p class="install-note">
              Paste the system prompt from <code>AGENTS.md</code> at the start
              of your session. Tell Claude where the skills folder is. Run
              intake. Same result. Same vault.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="install-cta">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="https://github.com/701am/earned-media-skills">
          Clone the repository
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <p class="install-license">
          MIT licensed · Use in client work, products, forks · Pull requests welcome
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 08 — CODA ════ -->
  <section class="skills-section skills-section--coda">
    <div class="coda-inner">
      <p class="coda-aphorism">★ Earned media that earns it ★</p>
      <p class="coda-p">
        We give this away because the alternative — every PR firm in the world
        running its own brittle, hand-coded version of the same workflows —
        produces worse pitches for every reporter on earth. The work is hard
        enough without that.
      </p>
      <p class="coda-p">
        Use it. Fork it. Tell us what we missed. Build a better follow-up
        sequence and open a pull request. Build a smarter newsjack and the
        next operator who clones this repo will inherit your work.
      </p>
      <p class="coda-sig">— D.K. · 701am · Filed at sunrise</p>
    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── MASTHEAD ─────── */
  .skills-masthead {
    padding: calc(var(--x1) + var(--x3)) var(--x1) var(--x1);
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    background: var(--paper);
  }
  .masthead-inner {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .skills-eyebrow {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.34em;
    color: var(--claret);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    font-weight: 600;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--x3);
  }
  .skills-rule {
    display: inline-block;
    width: 28px; height: 1px;
    background: var(--claret);
    opacity: 0.5;
  }
  .skills-title {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.02;
    letter-spacing: -0.035em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  .skills-title em {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 300;
  }
  .skills-deck {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 46ch;
    margin: 0 auto var(--x2);
  }
  .masthead-meta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--x4);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .meta-pill {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 4px 10px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .meta-dot { color: var(--rule-strong); }
  .masthead-cta {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--x2);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  /* ─────── SECTIONS ─────── */
  .skills-section {
    padding: var(--section-y) var(--x1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .skills-section--paper { background: var(--paper); }
  .skills-section--warm  { background: var(--paper-warm); }
  .skills-section--proclamation { background: var(--paper-deep); }
  .skills-section--install { background: var(--paper); }
  .skills-section--coda {
    background: var(--paper-warm);
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* ─────── § 01 — SCENE ─────── */
  .scene {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .scene-stamp {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: var(--x4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .scene-prose {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.1875rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .scene-prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .scene-prose.dropcap::first-letter {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    float: left;
    font-size: 4.5em;
    line-height: 0.85;
    margin: 0.05em 0.1em 0 -0.04em;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .scene-fold {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin: var(--x2) auto;
    max-width: 200px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--rule-strong);
    position: relative;
  }
  .scene-fold::before {
    content: "·";
    position: absolute;
    top: -10px;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    background: var(--paper);
    padding: 0 8px;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 18px;
  }
  .scene-prose--quiet {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
  }
  .scene-prose--quiet em {
    color: var(--claret);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ─────── § 02 — DIAGNOSIS ─────── */
  .diagnosis {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .diagnosis-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.04;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 18ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  .diagnosis-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); font-weight: 300; }
  .diagnosis-lede {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 36ch;
    margin: 0 auto var(--x1);
  }
  .diagnosis-label {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.30em;
    color: var(--claret);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding-bottom: var(--x4);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .diagnosis-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    padding: 0;
    counter-reset: diag-counter;
  }
  .diagnosis-list li {
    counter-increment: diag-counter;
    position: relative;
    padding: var(--x3) 0 var(--x3) 3rem;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .diagnosis-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .diagnosis-list li::before {
    content: counter(diag-counter, decimal-leading-zero);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    top: calc(var(--x3) + 4px);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--claret);
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
  }
  .diagnosis-list strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 600; }
  .diagnosis-close {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    line-height: 1.62;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: var(--x2) 0 0;
    padding-top: var(--x2);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .diagnosis-close em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }

  /* ─────── § 03 — REMEDY ─────── */
  .remedy {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .remedy-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x1);
    text-align: center;
    max-width: 28ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  .remedy-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); font-weight: 300; }
  .remedy-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    margin-top: var(--x1);
  }
  .remedy-col {
    padding: var(--x2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .remedy-col:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
  .remedy-col:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }
  .remedy-sub {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.2;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .remedy-col p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .remedy-col p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .remedy-col code,
  .install code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.88em;
    color: var(--claret);
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: 1px 6px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  /* ─────── § 04 — DESKS ─────── */
  .desks {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .desks-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x1);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .desks-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); font-weight: 300; }
  .desks-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    margin-top: var(--x1);
  }
  .desk {
    padding: var(--x2);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .desk:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
  .desk:nth-last-child(-n+2) { border-bottom: none; }
  .desk-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--claret);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x5);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
  }
  .desk-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.18;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    letter-spacing: -0.012em;
  }
  .desk-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .desk-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }

  /* ─────── § 05 — SHELF ─────── */
  .shelf-intro {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto var(--x1);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .shelf-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .shelf-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); font-weight: 300; }
  .shelf-deck {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 36ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .shelf-deck em { color: var(--claret); }
  .shelf {
    max-width: var(--measure-wide);
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .shelf-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 11rem 1fr;
    grid-template-rows: auto auto;
    gap: var(--x5) var(--x3);
    padding: var(--x2) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .shelf-row--highlight { background: var(--paper-soft); padding-left: var(--x3); padding-right: var(--x3); }
  .shelf-label {
    grid-row: 1 / span 2;
    align-self: start;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.32em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    padding-top: 4px;
  }
  .shelf-items {
    grid-column: 2;
    grid-row: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: var(--x5);
  }
  .shelf-item {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper-deep);
    padding: 4px 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .shelf-row--highlight .shelf-item {
    background: var(--claret);
    color: var(--paper-soft);
    border-color: var(--claret);
  }
  .shelf-note {
    grid-column: 2;
    grid-row: 2;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* ─────── § 06 — PROCLAMATION ─────── */
  .proclamation {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    padding: calc(var(--x1) + var(--x4)) var(--x1) var(--x1);
    position: relative;
    box-shadow: 0 14px 36px rgba(15, 14, 14, 0.08);
  }
  .proclamation::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px; left: 10px; right: 10px; bottom: 10px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(15, 14, 14, 0.08);
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .proc-stamp {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.30em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .proc-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.15;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .proc-h em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); font-weight: 300; }
  .proc-q {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.2vw, 2rem);
    line-height: 1.25;
    color: var(--claret);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .proc-q em { font-style: italic; }
  .proc-rule {
    width: 60px;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--claret);
    margin: var(--x3) auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .proc-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    max-width: 42ch;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  .proc-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .proc-sig {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin: var(--x3) 0 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  /* ─────── § 07 — INSTALL ─────── */
  .install {
    max-width: var(--measure);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .install-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x1);
    text-align: center;
  }
  .install-steps {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x1);
    padding: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .install-steps li {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 4rem 1fr;
    gap: var(--x3);
    padding: var(--x2) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .install-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .install-step-body h4 {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .install-code {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', ui-monospace, Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper-deep);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x4) var(--x3);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    overflow-x: auto;
    white-space: pre;
  }
  .install-note {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .install-cta {
    text-align: center;
    padding-top: var(--x2);
  }
  .install-license {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: var(--x3) 0 0;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* ─────── § 08 — CODA ─────── */
  .coda-inner {
    max-width: 36rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .coda-aphorism {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.30em;
    color: var(--claret);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
  }
  .coda-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x2);
  }
  .coda-sig {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    margin: var(--x2) 0 0;
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  /* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════
     RESPONSIVE — tablet (≤900px) → phone (≤720px) → small phone (≤420px)
     ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ */

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    /* Side-by-side grids collapse */
    .remedy-grid,
    .desks-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .remedy-col,
    .desk {
      border-right: none;
    }
    .remedy-col:nth-last-child(-n+2),
    .desk:nth-last-child(-n+2) {
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .remedy-col:last-child,
    .desk:last-child {
      border-bottom: none;
    }

    /* Shelf — collapse the label column earlier than the inherited 720 breakpoint */
    .shelf-row {
      grid-template-columns: 9rem 1fr;
      gap: var(--x4);
      padding: var(--x3) 0;
    }

    /* Briefing-style spacing tightens */
    .skills-section { padding: var(--x1) var(--x3); }
    .skills-masthead { padding: calc(var(--x1) + var(--x4)) var(--x3) var(--x3); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 720px) {
    /* Section padding — consistent breathing room */
    .skills-section { padding: var(--x1) var(--x3); }
    .skills-masthead { padding: var(--x2) var(--x3) var(--x3); }

    /* MASTHEAD */
    .skills-title {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 9vw, 3rem);
      letter-spacing: -0.028em;
      max-width: 14ch;
    }
    .skills-deck {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
      max-width: 36ch;
    }
    .masthead-meta {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: var(--x5);
      font-size: 10px;
      letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    }
    .meta-dot { display: none; }
    .masthead-cta {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: stretch;
      gap: var(--x4);
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 22rem;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
    .masthead-cta .btn-primary,
    .masthead-cta .btn-link {
      justify-content: center;
      width: 100%;
    }

    /* SCENE — § 01 */
    .scene-stamp {
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      padding-bottom: var(--x5);
    }
    .scene-prose {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }
    .scene-prose.dropcap::first-letter {
      font-size: 3.25em;
      margin: 0.04em 0.08em 0 -0.03em;
    }
    .scene-prose--quiet {
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    /* DIAGNOSIS — § 02 */
    .diagnosis-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 7vw, 2.25rem);
      letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    }
    .diagnosis-lede {
      font-size: 1.0625rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
      max-width: 32ch;
    }
    .diagnosis-label {
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
      margin-bottom: var(--x5);
    }
    .diagnosis-list li {
      padding: var(--x4) 0 var(--x4) 2.25rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .diagnosis-list li::before {
      top: calc(var(--x4) + 2px);
      font-size: 10px;
    }
    .diagnosis-close {
      font-size: 1rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    /* REMEDY — § 03 */
    .remedy-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 7vw, 2.25rem);
      max-width: 22ch;
    }
    .remedy-col {
      padding: var(--x3) 0;
    }
    .remedy-sub {
      font-size: 1.1875rem;
    }
    .remedy-col p { font-size: 0.9375rem; }

    /* DESKS — § 04 */
    .desks-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 7vw, 2.25rem);
    }
    .desk { padding: var(--x3) 0; }
    .desk-h {
      font-size: 1.3125rem;
      line-height: 1.2;
    }
    .desk-p { font-size: 0.9375rem; line-height: 1.55; }

    /* SHELF — § 05 — stack the label above its items on phones */
    .shelf-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 7vw, 2.25rem);
    }
    .shelf-deck {
      font-size: 1rem;
      max-width: 32ch;
    }
    .shelf {
      margin: var(--x3) auto 0;
    }
    .shelf-row {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      grid-template-rows: auto auto auto;
      gap: var(--x5);
      padding: var(--x3) 0;
    }
    .shelf-row--highlight {
      padding: var(--x3);
      margin: 0 calc(-1 * var(--x4));
    }
    .shelf-label {
      grid-row: 1;
      grid-column: 1;
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.28em;
      padding-top: 0;
    }
    .shelf-items {
      grid-row: 2;
      grid-column: 1;
      gap: 6px;
    }
    .shelf-item {
      font-size: 12px;
      padding: 3px 8px;
    }
    .shelf-note {
      grid-row: 3;
      grid-column: 1;
      font-size: 14px;
      line-height: 1.45;
      max-width: 100%;
    }

    /* PROCLAMATION — § 06 */
    .proclamation {
      padding: var(--x2) var(--x3) var(--x2);
      max-width: 100%;
    }
    .proclamation::before {
      top: 6px; left: 6px; right: 6px; bottom: 6px;
    }
    .proc-stamp {
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    }
    .proc-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 6vw, 1.875rem);
      line-height: 1.15;
    }
    .proc-q {
      font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 5.5vw, 1.625rem);
      line-height: 1.25;
    }
    .proc-rule { margin: var(--x2) auto; }
    .proc-p {
      font-size: 0.9375rem;
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    /* INSTALL — § 07 */
    .install-h {
      font-size: clamp(1.875rem, 7vw, 2.25rem);
    }
    .install-steps li {
      grid-template-columns: 2.5rem 1fr;
      gap: var(--x4);
      padding: var(--x3) 0;
    }
    .install-num {
      font-size: 1.875rem;
    }
    .install-step-body h4 {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
      margin-bottom: var(--x5);
    }
    .install-code {
      font-size: 11px;
      padding: var(--x4) var(--x4);
      line-height: 1.4;
      white-space: pre-wrap;       /* allow long URLs to wrap on phones */
      overflow-wrap: anywhere;
      word-break: break-word;
    }
    .install-note { font-size: 0.9375rem; }
    .install-license {
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    }

    /* CODA — § 08 */
    .coda-aphorism {
      font-size: 9px;
      letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    }
    .coda-p { font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 420px) {
    /* MASTHEAD — shrink the headline one more notch */
    .skills-title {
      font-size: clamp(2rem, 10vw, 2.5rem);
    }
    .meta-pill {
      font-size: 9px;
      padding: 3px 8px;
    }

    /* SCENE */
    .scene-prose { font-size: 1rem; }
    .scene-prose.dropcap::first-letter { font-size: 2.75em; }

    /* DIAGNOSIS */
    .diagnosis-h { font-size: 1.75rem; }
